{
  "stem": "11174.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I would say they were not typical.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Almost every was a little different.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But the normal routine was getting up in the morning and go to beth midrash to learn, and then you go for breakfast.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then you go back to beth midrash, and then you're a little sleepy, so you-- you took-- you open the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "You put your hand-- the head on top of the hand to take a little snooze, and then you learned again.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And after that, if you had a big [NON-ENGLISH], which means you-- so you kept on going until [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "If not, you had a few fellows that also didn't feel like too much to-- to stick to the learning, so they talk.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There wasn't anything else to do in that little town.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The schooling as the teenager-- first of all, I was 10 years old when-- my zayde had a gabbai who was like his personal servant and everything.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he asked my father, you complain that-- now I had, as far as learning, I had like it's an expression in-- in Hebrew, a-- a Talmudical expression [HEBREW].",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Sometimes you're normal, sometimes you're not normal.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My father said it to me.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If I set out to learn, I could have learned without stop, practically 18, 20 hours that he begged me to stop, because he was afraid I-- [INAUDIBLE] And if I didn't feel like learning, he could chop me up and I wouldn't.",
      "word_count": 43
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So this was unfortunately, my, my [? stubborn ?] made him very unhappy.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So-- but-- but at 10 years old, that one suggested to my father, because he told him, you know, complained.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He says, why don't you send him to yeshiva?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So he sent me to Krakow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I was only 10 years old.",
      "word_count": 6
    }
  ],
